descript.abstract: This geographic dataclass of the Alachua County roadway system represents all named roadways of Alachua County, Florida and their address ranges. The area of extent for this dataset is countywide. All features are uniquely symbolized based on the CLASS_Code attribute.
descript.supplinf: All road centerlines were compiled as single lines, except I-75, where the centerline defines each side of the interstate compiled to represent the direction of travel. All other roads were compiled in a simplified manner to best describe the road network to its fullest extent. Double lane roads, single lane roads, highways, and city streets have one centerline down the approximate geographic center. The centerlines were pulled across medians and road partitions where they existed. Centerlines were compiled to the end of cul-de-sacs and terminate at the road edge. Road centerlines are broken where they intersect each other. All features are uniquely symbolized based on the CLASS_CODE attribute. The CLASS_CODE based on Road Type: 1- city streets with name designation 2 - interstate with limited access. 3- U.S. Highways. 4- State Roads. 5- County Roads. 6 and 0- Private and unnamed roads. All, but 2,6 and 0 road classes are populated with address ranges. All roads were compiled the extent of the orthophoto coverage. No attempt was made to clip roads at the county boundary.
descript.purpose: To serve as base information for use in GIS systems for a variety of planning and analytical purposes; To show location and address ranges of all named roadways (such as: City and County roads, US and Interstate highways) in Alachua County, FL. Centerline address ranges have been added for geocoding purposes.
